JavaScript Interview Syllabus

1. Variables and Scoping
   - var, let, const
   - Hoisting, Temporal Dead Zone, Execution Context

2. Branching Statements
   - if-else, Nested if-else, Ladder if-else
   - switch Case
   - Loops for, while, do-while, for-of, for-in

3. Functions in JavaScript
   - Regular Functions
   - Function Expressions
   - Arrow Functions
   - IIFE Immediately Invoked Function Expressions

4. Arrays
   - Methods push, pop, slice, splice, map, filter, forEach, find, findIndex, reduce

5. Objects
   - Object Literals
   - Constructor Functions
   - Reference Copy, Shallow Copy, Deep Copy, Structured Cloning
   - Spread Operator

6. DOM Manipulation
   - Methods getElementById, getElementsByClassName, getElementsByTagName, createElement, removeElement
   - Event Handling addEventListener, Event Bubbling, Event Capturing, stopPropagation

7. Asynchronous JavaScript
   - Callbacks, Callback Hell
   - setTimeout and setInterval

8. Promises
   - Handling Promises
   - Promise Chaining and Avoiding Promise Hell

9. JSON
   - JSON parse, JSON stringify

10. Async Await
   - Async Functions
   - Exception Handling in Async Code

11. Classes and Inheritance
   - ES6 Classes
   - Inheritance

12. Storage APIs
   - Local Storage
   - Session Storage
   - Cookies

13. Date and Time
   - Working with Date and Time in JavaScript
   - UTC Time

14. APIs
   - Fetch API
   - Axios

15. this Keyword
   - Understanding this in Different Execution Contexts

16. Modules in JavaScript
   - ES6 Modules import and export

17. Strings
   - String Methods includes, split, replace, trim, etc.
   - Template Literals Template Strings

18. Destructuring
   - Array Destructuring
   - Object Destructuring

